title: For Sale:  Taurus PT92 Pistol
postcontent:
I am selling my Taurus PT 92 AFS pistol in combat matte finish. Comes with a Fobius Paddle Holster It is hard to find this finish on this pistol. I only take cash locally, would consider an FFL Transfer  out of town. Please text about buying the gun. Serious offers only please.

5 in barrel
17+1 Capacity

A large contract for the Beretta 92 was with the Brazilian army, for which Beretta set up a factory in Brazil. This factory was later sold to the Brazilian gunmaker Taurus (Forjas Taurus S/A ). Taurus makes these pistols (called the PT92) without the need for a license from Beretta since their design is based on the original Beretta 92, whose patents have since expired.

Like the Beretta, the Taurus PT92 utilizes the open-slide design where the upper portion of the slide is cut away exposing much of the barrel itself. The original PT92 was exactly like the original Beretta 92, though it was also unusual for the time in that it featured a squared trigger guard for supporting the index finger of the opposite hand while firing, a feature which was subsequently introduced to the Beretta 92 with the 92SB-F (92F) model in 1985.

Other versions of the PT92 include the PT99, which has an adjustable rear sight and a taller front sight, the compact PT92C version, and the PT100 and PT101, which are .40 S&W versions of the PT92 and PT99, respectively.

The Taurus PT92 has undergone many revisions in design since it was originally produced in the mid-1980s. Early PT92s and PT99s did not feature the third safety position decocker that is now standard; this feature was added to the second-generation models in the early-1990s, which also included the three-dot sights found on the Beretta 92F. A third revision in the late-90s changed the grip and slide design (which now has wider cocking serrations than PT92s manufactured before 1997).

More recently (as of 2005), Taurus has begun manufacturing the PT92 with built-in accessory rails on the frame, a feature found on the newer Beretta M9A1, a military upgrade of the Beretta 92F from which the PT92 is derived

title: For Sale:  CZ 75 Pre B 9mm Completely restored with NO Import Marks, VZ Frag Black Cherry grips $750
postcontent:
I have for sale an excellent CZ 75 Pre B 9mm pistol that has been completely restored.....the RIGHT way! Pre B means before the B model or without a firing pin block equating to a much smoother trigger pull and fewer moving parts. The oldest model apart from the 1975 Short Rail. I have noticed several of these coming up for sale lately, many shoddily ressurected guns with a cheap duracote job and thrown on gunbroker. I am asking the same price, but if you take a close look my gun is worlds better in quality. For starters my gun had NO import marks like all those aim surplus and cdi guns out there. And unlike the flipper specials, this gun was refinished by DOA arms in Virginia Beach the right way. The devil is in the good prep work. 3 stages of stripping including media blasting and alkali strip are performed. Then Cerakoting with the thermal baked formula, not the thinner air dry cheaper mix. Afterwards, the gun was reassembled by me including upgrades in springs and an internal polishing. The stainless steel barrel is also polished. From the outer view this gun is bone stock. Lastly it's wearing a brand new set VZ Frag Black Cherry G10 grips. Original CZ grips are included as well. 1 hard to find Pre B 16 round mag included. The secret to finding excellent mags for a good price: CZ SP-01 mags fit perfect, match the grip contour and hold 18 rounds. Buy them. You will not find a nicer CZ 75 Pre B for anywhere near this price if you look closely to the detail work. More pics available via text if requested.

title: For Sale:  RCBS primer catcher - 3D printed, new & improved version!
postcontent:
One of the most annoying things with my Rock Chucker IV is the primer catch. Cumbersome to put on, not enough capacity and plenty primers don't even make it into the collector.

I fixed this by improving an existing design for a new primer catcher design. Much, much better than what RCBS provides... There is one person on ebay selling those in a different (inferior) design - my version has a few significant improvements.

The improvement are making it more stable on the press (smaller gaps between catcher and press) and a clamp on version versus the one that tries to lock the catcher down with a spent .22 case.

The one I sell also comes with the tube.

But, to set expectations - this is not coming out of a mold, it will have minor cosmetic imperfections (3D printing in the consumer market simply are limited in regards to resolution). It will be working perfectly fine and will fit your Rock Chucker IV as advertised.

Have a look at the pictures and let me know if you have questions. 

Price is $20 and includes shipping in the lower 48.
Payment via money order, certified personal check, cash, 1oz silver and local pickup/cash only. 

Also, if you got anything gun related you would like to trade, I am open for that as well. Also can add cash on my side (e.g. nice derringer or revolver or reloading powder, primers and so on...)
